# Firebase CLI - Quick Command Reference

## ðŸš€ Quickest Way (Copy-Paste Commands)

### 1. Install Firebase CLI
```powershell
npm install -g firebase-tools
```

### 2. Login to Firebase
```powershell
firebase login
```

### 3. Import appSettings
```powershell
firebase --project=accreditex-79c08 firestore:set appSettings/default --merge < appSettings.json
```

### 4. Verify
```powershell
firebase --project=accreditex-79c08 firestore:get appSettings/default
```

### 5. Refresh App
Refresh your browser - app should load now!

---

## ðŸ“ Manual Steps (Firebase Console)

### Via Web Browser (No CLI Needed)

1. **Open Firebase Console**
   ```
   https://console.firebase.google.com/project/accreditex-79c08/firestore/data
   ```

2. **Click "+ Start collection"**
   - Collection ID: `appSettings`
   - Document ID: `default`
   - Add fields from `appSettings.json`

3. **Refresh your app**
   - App should load successfully

---

## ðŸ” Useful Firebase CLI Commands

### List all collections
```bash
firebase --project=accreditex-79c08 firestore:inspect
```

### Get a specific document
```bash
firebase --project=accreditex-79c08 firestore:get appSettings/default
```

### Delete a document
```bash
firebase --project=accreditex-79c08 firestore:delete appSettings/default
```

### Import/Export collection
```bash
# Export
firebase --project=accreditex-79c08 firestore:export backup

# Import
firebase --project=accreditex-79c08 firestore:import backup
```

---

## ðŸ“Š What Each Field Does

| Field | Purpose | Example |
|-------|---------|---------|
| appName | App title shown in UI | "AccreditEx" |
| logoUrl | Logo image URL | "" (empty for now) |
| primaryColor | Brand color in hex | "#4f46e5" (purple) |
| defaultLanguage | Default UI language | "en" or "ar" |
| defaultUserRole | Role for new users | "TeamMember" |
| passwordPolicy | Password requirements | {minLength: 8, ...} |
| globeSettings | 3D globe appearance | {baseColor, scale, ...} |
| appearance | UI theme settings | {compactMode, showAnimations, ...} |
| notifications | Notification preferences | {emailNotifications, ...} |
| accessibility | Accessibility options | {fontSize, highContrast, ...} |

